SIMPLE: hearken
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hearken
<hw>Heark"en</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rk"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hearkened</conjf>
<pr>(-'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hearkening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>hercnen</ets>,
<ets>hercnien</ets>, AS. <ets>hercnian</ets>, <ets>heorcnian</ets>, fr.
<ets>hi⟦eacute⟧ran</ets>, <ets>h⟦ymac⟧ran</ets>, to hear; akin to OD.
<ets>harcken</ets>, <ets>horcken</ets>, LG. <ets>harken</ets>,
<ets>horken</ets>, G. <ets>horchen</ets>. See <er>Hear</er>, and cf.
<er>Hark</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To listen; to lend the ear; to
attend to what is uttered; to give heed; to hear, in order to obey or
comply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Furies <qex>hearken</qex>, and their snakes uncurl.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hearken</qex>, O Israel, unto the statutes and unto the
judgments, which I teach you.</q> <rj><qau>Deut. iv. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inquire; to seek information.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hearken</xex> after their
offense.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To attend; listen; hear; heed. See
<er>Attend</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos></syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hearken</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hearken
<hw>Heark"en</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hear by
listening.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[She] <qex>hearkened</qex> now and then⟦br⟧
Some little whispering and soft groaning sound.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give heed to; to hear attentively.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The King of Naples . . . <qex>hearkens</qex> my brother's
suit.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To hearken out</b></col>, <cd>to search out.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If you find none, you must <qex>hearken out</qex> a vein and
buy.</q> <rj><qau>B. Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hearkener</ent>⟦br⟧
